Yemen’s Saleh to Resign, WSJ Says, Citing Unidentified Presidential Aide

-- B y   A n n   H u g h e y
-- 
2011-04-23T16:43:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-23/yemen-s-saleh-to-resign-wsj-says-citing-unidentified-presidential-aide.html
Yemen’s President Ali Abdullah
Saleh has agreed to step down from power after 30 days, the Wall
Street Journal reported, citing an unidentified presidential
aide.  The agreement, which was made in exchange for immunity for
Saleh and his close relatives, was brokered by neighboring Arab
countries  Saudi Arabia  and the  United Arab Emirates , the Journal
reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ann Hughey at 
 ahughey@bloomberg.net  